metaphor: Don't forget to wrap the presents like I showed you!
scene_description: Each input grid contains a number of presents, set along a differently colored background. Each present is rectangular. Anything in the input grid that is not a present or connected to a present, is a key. Each present has a number of points that represent connectors.
literal_instruction: Each input scene has a set of rectangles that are uniformely colored with the exception of one or more isolacted pixels. Each input scene also has an object that is not rectangular, a key of sorts. The color of the isolated pixels in the rectangle is the same as the center pixel of the key. They key serves as an instruction for how to extend the isolated pixels in the rectangles, which is shown in the output scenes.
